import pandas as pd

iris = inputs[0]
key_table1 = pd.DataFrame({'group1':['A','B']})
key_table2 = pd.DataFrame({'group2':[1,2]})
iris['key'] = 0
key_table1['key'] = 0
key_table2['key'] = 0

out = iris.merge(key_table1, how='left', on='key').merge(key_table2, how='left', on='key').drop(columns=['key'])
